programme.title: Blithe Spirit (1945)
programme.desc: David Lean directed Noel Coward's fantasy about a ghost returning to disrupt her husband's second marriage.

programme.title: Our Town (1940)
programme.desc: A chronicle of small-town life in New England before WWI centers on the daughter of a local newspaper editor and the son of a town doctor who fall in love, endure a difficult courtship, marry and experience their share of tragedy.

programme.title: A Family Affair (1937)
programme.desc: The first entry in the Hardy Family film series, which featured 15 sequels, revolves around patriarch Judge Hardy's reelection, which is threatened by a divorce scandal involving his daughter. Lionel Barrymore stars as the judge, but was replaced by Lewis Stone in the sequels.

programme.title: You're Only Young Once (1938)
programme.desc: Second entry in the Hardy Family series has them vacationing on California's Catalina Island, where the judge is angling for swordfish, young Andy is angling for dates with a local lovely and daughter Marian gets involved with a handsome lifeguard.

programme.title: Judge Hardy's Children (1938)
programme.desc: When the Hardy family goes to Washington on political business, young Andy suffers through his first affair, and of all the girls to involve in such a mess, he picks a diplomat's daughter.

programme.title: Love Finds Andy Hardy (1938)
programme.desc: Andy finds himself the target of a lot of female attention as he prepares for the country club Christmas party, to which he had originally wanted to bring his girlfriend, Polly, until she announced she'd be going out of town for the holidays.

programme.title: Out West With the Hardys (1938)
programme.desc: When the Hardy family embarks on a vacation, the expected problems pursue them. Lewis Stone, Mickey Rooney. Marian: Cecilia Parker. Jake: Virginia Weidler. Polly: Ann Rutherford. Mrs. Hardy: Fay Holden. Aunt Milly: Sara Haden. Dennis: Don Castle. Ray: Gordon Jones. Dora: Nana Bryant. Northcote: Ralph Morgan. Brown: Tom Neal. Thomas: Anthony Allan. George B. Seitz directed.

programme.title: The Hardys Ride High (1939)
programme.desc: When the Hardy family arrives in Detroit to claim an inheritance, Andy falls for a show girl, and the whole small town clan finds it difficult to adjust to high society life.

programme.title: Andy Hardy Gets Spring Fever (1939)
programme.desc: The seventh entry in the series sees high-schooler Andy rehearsing for a class play and becoming infatuated with the dramatics teacher.

programme.title: Judge Hardy and Son (1939)
programme.desc: A small-town judge with a good heart tries to save an elderly couple from their impending eviction, all while simultaneously coping with his wife being sick.

programme.title: Andy Hardy Meets Debutante (1940)
programme.desc: Young Andy falls head over heels for a Manhattan debutante, and puts himself into debt trying to court her before getting sick of the aristocratic lifestyle.

programme.title: Andy Hardy's Private Secretary (1941)
programme.desc: Andy, about to graduate from high school, tries to help an unfortunate girl.

programme.title: Life Begins for Andy Hardy (1941)
programme.desc: The 10th entry in the series picks up with small-towner Andy fresh out of high school and skipping college in order to seek his fortune in New York City, where he finds the going is rough.

programme.title: The Courtship of Andy Hardy (1942)
programme.desc: The 12th entry in the series has Andy trying to help the shy teenage daughter of quarreling parents by escorting her to the prom.

programme.title: Andy Hardy's Double Life (1942)
programme.desc: Andy (Mickey Rooney) gets the vamp treatment from a college girl (Esther Williams). Lewis Stone, Fay Holden, Ann Rutherford, Cecilia Parker, Sara Haden. Jeff: William Lundigan. Sue: Susan Peters. Standard dilemmas. Directed by George B. Seitz.

programme.title: Andy Hardy's Blonde Trouble (1944)
programme.desc: Entry in the series sends the irrepressible Andy to college, where he becomes involved with beautiful identical twin sisters and soon finds himself in hot water with the administration.

programme.title: Love Laughs at Andy Hardy (1946)
programme.desc: A WWII veteran returns home and, after being welcomed back with open arms, begins a romance with a college student. When she breaks his heart, he has a deep conversation with his father, and soon finds the strength to give love another chance.

programme.title: Andy Hardy Comes Home (1958)
programme.desc: With his wife and children, Andy pays a visit to his old home town. Mickey Rooney, Patricia Breslin. Mother: Fay Holden. Aunt Milly: Sara Haden. Marian: Cecilia Parker. Andy Jr.: Teddy Rooney. Chandler: Vaughn Taylor. Betty: Pat Cawley. Beezy: Joey Forman. Directed by Howard W. Koch.

programme.title: That Way with Women (1947)
programme.desc: A tycoon forced into retirement poses as a humble gardener and helps out an honest gas-station owner who is being pressured out of business by corrupt officials.

programme.title: The Maltese Falcon (1941)
programme.desc: After his partner is killed, a PI is hired to track down a stolen artifact, a priceless, jewel-laden statuette of a black bird. His investigation leads him to become embroiled in a series of crosses and double-crosses that lead right back to his murdered comrade.

programme.title: Background to Danger (1943)
programme.desc: Barton, an American agent working undercover in neutral Turkey during WWII, receives documents of plans for a supposed Russian invasion. Soon Barton and two Russian siblings must combat a ruthless Nazi agent. Based on the novel by Eric Ambler.

programme.title: Conflict (1945)
programme.desc: This psychological thriller stars Humphrey Bogart as a clever husband who hatches a plan to murder his wife so he can marry her sister.

programme.title: The Mask of Dimitrios (1944)
programme.desc: Mystery novelist Cornelius Leyden is on vacation in Istanbul when the body of master criminal Makropoulos washes up on shore. Leyden becomes inspired to learn and tell the story of Makropoulos' rise to power, traveling across Europe to uncover secrets and stitch together the criminal's narrative. Based on the novel "A Coffin for Dimitrios" by Eric Ambler.

programme.title: Three Strangers (1946)
programme.desc: Two men and one woman form a strange partnership on the Chinese New Year.

programme.title: The Verdict (1946)
programme.desc: After a Scotland Yard detective loses his job after a faulty conviction, he must battle his successor after becoming embroiled in a murder investigation, in this "locked room" mystery set in 1890s London.

programme.title: Le Samourai (1967)
programme.desc: After carrying out a flawlessly planned hit, Jef Costello, a contract killer with samurai instincts, finds himself caught between a persistent police investigator and a ruthless employer, and not even his armor of fedora and trench coat can protect him.

programme.title: 3 Women (1977)
programme.desc: Young, awkward Pinky gets a job at a spa in the California desert and forms a dependent bond with her new, outgoing roommate, even adopting some of her traits. Things take a turn when Pinky discovers her roommate with the husband of a local artist.

programme.title: Blood Simple (1984)
programme.desc: A dishonest private eye is hired to murder a bar owner's cheating wife and her lover. After some slight modifications to better suit his interests and a surprise double-cross, things spiral out of control.
